              "description": "Perform a fitness assessment, starting with a 12-minute Cooper Run Test to estimate your VO2 Max. Follow up with bodyweight exercises (e.g., push-ups, squats, planks) to establish initial strength baselines, recording maximum reps and hold times. This data will serve as a quantifiable metric for tracking progress.",
