              "description": "Learn to manage Git branches more effectively by deleting merged or finished branches locally and remotely (`git branch -d`, `git push origin --delete`). Additionally, learn `git stash` to temporarily save uncommitted changes, allowing you to switch branches cleanly. This keeps your repository organized and efficient.",
