              "title": "Introduction to Neural Networks: Perceptrons & Activation Functions",
              "description": "Begin your journey into deep learning with the fundamental building blocks of neural networks: the perceptron. Understand how it simulates biological neurons and the role of activation functions (e.g., sigmoid, ReLU) in introducing non-linearity. Draw a simple perceptron and outline its computational steps. This lays the groundwork for more complex neural architectures.",
