              "description": "Practice the full GitHub collaboration workflow: forking an open-source repository (or a dummy one), cloning your fork, making changes, committing, pushing to your fork, and then creating a Pull Request (PR) back to the original repository. This simulates contributing to larger projects and practicing professional code submission protocols.",
