              "description": "Set up a new GitHub repository for the project. Configure Git locally, including global user settings. Create an initial `README.md` file outlining the project's purpose and an `.gitignore` file to prevent unnecessary files (e.g., IDE files, dataset archives, compiled artifacts) from being committed. This establishes version control from day one, which is critical for collaborative and robust development.",
